The paper discusses the application of logic-based abduction in artificial intelligence, which is a topic covered in the cs.AI sub-category. The paper specifically focuses on propositional abduction, which involves propositional logic, and thus could also be categorized under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The use of SAT solvers and hitting sets also suggests a connection to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes algorithmic improvements, which could fall under the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses complexity and performance improvements, which could also be relevant to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
